def: Adorned with sculptured leaves and branches.
Not true in opinion or doctrine; false.-- n.
The middle bark of a tree; the green layer of bark, usuallysoon covered by the outer or corky layer, and obliterated.
Same as Cumin.Ye pay tithe of mint, and cummin. Matt. xxiii. 23.
In the time of; as long as the action or existence of; as,during life; during the space of a year.
To hike one's self; specif., to go with exertion or effort; totramp; to march laboriously. [Dial. or Colloq.] "If you persist inheaving and hiking like this."  Kipling.
Effective motion; also, mechanism; as, the breech action of agun.
The arrangement of feathers in definite areas.
The fragrant gum resin of various species of Boswellia;Oriental frankincense.

On the right-hand side of a shield, i. e., towards the righthand of its wearer. To a spectator in front, as in a pictorialrepresentation, this would be the left side. Dexter chief, or Dexterpoint (Her.), a point in the dexter upper corner of the shield, beingin the dexter extremity of the chief, as A in the cut.-- Dexter base, a point in the dexter lower part or base of theshield, as B in the cut.
Hook-billed; having the upper mandible longer than the lower.
